photo.description:
this looks like a cricket/grasshopper but Its the biggest and wierdest I've ever seen..its body is about 3" long and an inch deep. it was walking up a wall at night. it made no attempt to jump even when handled..not typical cricket behavour..took in Bulgaria, any one know what it could be?

photo.description: we got a glimps of a Red just after we parked the car, we walked a couple of mile through the woods trying to get another, chris mcloughlin managed to get a few shots of one on the run but I missed it, after a couple of hours I was getting desperate for a shot of one of these so we decided to pick our spot and drop a few magic peanuts and let the squirrels do the walking and come to us..it worked like a dream, chris was getting them with a 100mm macro.. see www.flickr.com/photos/madyorke/6867450316/

photo.title: Red Squirrel (Sciurus vulgaris)
photo.description: A great day out with Chris mcloughlin landscaping when we spotted this little chap..another first for me.

photo.title: Bank Vole Pout
photo.description: this is my favourite shot of a bank vole out of a few hundred that I've taken over the past 2 weeks ..love the expression on his face .. plus a couple more that I like in comments.
